    ```javascript
function maxPoints(s, x, y) {
    let points = 0;
    for (let i = 1; i < s.length; ++i) {
        if (s[i] === s[i - 1]) {
            points += Math.max(x, y);
            s = s.substring(0, i) + '#' + s.substring(i + 1);
        }
    }
    return points;
}
```

    The provided code iterates through the string, starting from the second character comparing it with the previous character. If the two consecutive characters are the same, it adds the maximum value of the given integers x and y to the points. To make sure that we don't reuse the character again, the element is altered by assigning it '#' (C++, Java, Python) or by replacing it with '#' in the string (JavaScript). The algorithm finally returns the points gained after applying the operations. The complexity of the algorithm is O(n) where n is the length of the string.

